title: New York City Bans TikTok on Government-Owned Devices
description: The ban extends to some of the popular accounts run by the city.

title: Kansas Newspaper Raid: Seized Items to Be Returned to Marion County Record
description: The raid of the newspaper, The Marion County Record, has drawn condemnation from First Amendment advocates.

title: When Hackers Descended to Test A.I., They Found Flaws Aplenty
description: The hackers had the blessing of the White House and leading A.I. companies, which want to learn about vulnerabilities before those with nefarious intentions do.

title: The A.I. Industry’s Desperate Hunt for GPUs Amid a Chip Shortage
description: To power artificial-intelligence products, start-ups and investors are taking extraordinary measures to obtain critical chips known as graphics processing units, or GPUs.

title: Google Tests an A.I. Assistant That Offers Life Advice
description: The tech giant is evaluating tools that would use artificial intelligence to perform tasks that some of its researchers have said should be avoided.

title: Intel Acquisition of Tower Semiconductor Is Scuttled by China
description: Intel calls off its planned acquisition of Tower Semiconductor, an Israeli chip maker, after waiting in vain for 18 months for a review by Chinese regulators.
